<item>
            <title>[OAK-5205] Lucene index causes many split documents</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-5205</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Because of changes introduced with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2392&quot; title=&quot;[DocumentMK] Garbage Collect older revisions of binary properties in main document&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2392&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2392&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the lucene index causes many split documents on the file segments.gen. This file is overwritten whenever the index is updated. With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2392&quot; title=&quot;[DocumentMK] Garbage Collect older revisions of binary properties in main document&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2392&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2392&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, each change causes a new split document even though the binary is less than 100 bytes in size.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13024716">OAK-5205</key>
            <summary>Lucene index causes many split documents</summary>
